    My father, a WW II vet, and I disagreed quite a bit about our country's involvment in the War.  After much soul-searching, when I was a junior in college I told him that I had no intention of ever going to Vietnam.  He stopped talking to me and didn't say another word to me until the day I got married, about a year and half later.<br>
    It took him another 15 years to admit our country was wrong to get involved in Vietnam.<br>

